The regex: `\b(?:goggle|scissor|plier|tong|tweezer|trouser|pant|pantie|clothe|billiard|bowl|card|dart|skittle|draught|diabete|measle|mump|rabie|ricket|shingle|alm|fece|bowel|sud|entrail|electronic|outskirt|odd|tropic|riche|surrounding|thank|heroic|remain|amend)s\b`

This matches words like `tropics`, `odds`, `alms`, etc. and returns them unchanged.

In mutated version, `tropic` → `""`, so `tropics` won't match. Let me actually test what `plural("tropics")` returns in each case by checking if the empty string changes the regex matching for `tropics` specifically.

